About the Artist

Bill Coedy is a contemporary artist based in the Kootenay region of British Columbia, where the dramatic mountain landscapes and pristine waterways serve as endless inspiration for his work.

His paintings capture the raw beauty and spiritual essence of the Pacific Northwest, translating the movement of rivers, the stillness of alpine peaks, and the ever-changing light across mountain valleys into vivid, expressive compositions.

Working primarily in acrylics and oils, Bill's distinctive style blends representational elements with abstract techniques, creating works that evoke both the grandeur of nature and the intimate connection we feel with wild places.

"Every stream tells a story. Every mountain holds a memory. I paint to preserve these moments of connection with the land." Bill Coedy
